(287964, 8752, 287942, 'Ahnab', 6111, '', 1344611798, '[QUOTE=Enigmatic Desires;287942]...i thought the caracal had a 2nd strike capability.[/QUOTE]\n\nThe only way a gun has a "Second Strike" capability is when it is able to cock and then discharge the firing mechanism in a single trigger pull, i.e. double action. This is very common in hammer-fired pistols, but not so in striker-fired guns. The Caracal, Glock and the Styer M9 pistols all lack the DA mode, hence no "Second Strike". The Walther P99, and by extension the Canik55 TP-9, come with the DA mode; hence they not only have "Second Strike" capability but also come equipped with a decocker.', 1, 1, '110.36.195.23', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
